03:40.460 --> 03:45.060
What chemistry actually works and which chemistry doesn't work so well.

03:45.060 --> 03:51.940
Over the last perhaps 15, 20 years, biology has become involved for the first time.

03:51.940 --> 03:56.980
Until then, surprisingly, biologists had almost nothing to say on the origin of life.

03:56.980 --> 04:01.620
It was dismissed as armchair speculation of the worst kind, not science at all.

04:01.620 --> 04:05.900
Whereas the chemists were thinking, OK, here's an interesting challenge in synthetic chemistry.

04:05.900 --> 04:10.020
Can we make the nucleotides that make up DNA or RNA? Can we make the sugars?

04:10.020 --> 04:13.380
Can we make the lipids to make membranes and so on?

04:13.380 --> 04:17.940
It was a valid question in synthetic chemistry and they've made all of these things.

04:17.940 --> 04:23.420
