48:04.180 --> 48:07.020
That's the first position of the codon.

48:07.020 --> 48:09.700
If we organize this by the first position of the codon,

48:09.700 --> 48:13.780
so a G or an A at that first position or a C or a U,

48:13.780 --> 48:17.300
this is the second position of the anticodon.

48:17.620 --> 48:20.820
And this is the hydrophobicity.

48:20.820 --> 48:26.580
And so the V is valine, it's a very hydrophobic amino acid.

48:26.580 --> 48:30.940
And it's encoded, the colors changed here, unfortunately, this is now an A.

48:30.940 --> 48:36.340
So valine is encoded at the second position of the anticodon by an A,

48:36.340 --> 48:39.260
