48:52.100 --> 48:57.980
So we see this relationship between how much water-loving or water-hating they are.

48:57.980 --> 49:01.300
It suggests they're snuggling up to each other in some way.

49:02.460 --> 49:06.660
It's less strong if we're further away, if we're looking at C and U,

49:06.660 --> 49:10.380
so these were the ones that were further away at the first position.

49:10.380 --> 49:12.620
There is a relationship, but it's not very impressive.

49:12.620 --> 49:16.380
But these first two, it really does look as if there are direct interactions

49:16.380 --> 49:19.660
between amino acids and the bases that code for them.

49:19.660 --> 49:25.220
And this is a third position, and this is what's called an inverted codon table.

49:25.220 --> 49:28.700
So first of all, most people would think that the third position

49:28.700 --> 49:30.940
