49:40.980 --> 49:44.860
But where it's coloured, these are not redundant.

49:44.860 --> 49:47.980
It's a single amino acid is encoded by that.

49:47.980 --> 49:51.460
So you can see immediately that it's not a random patterning.

49:51.460 --> 49:55.380
The redundancy itself is not random in the genetic code.

49:55.380 --> 49:58.580
And if I just consider one example, so this is glutamate,

49:58.580 --> 50:02.300
