And when we're digesting food and burning food,

01:01:54.380 --> 01:01:55.700
it's going straight here.

01:01:55.700 --> 01:01:58.980
So although this is the interface with the world,

01:01:58.980 --> 01:02:01.020
really what's happening is going on here.

01:02:01.020 --> 01:02:03.500
Any problems that we have in relation to the world,

01:02:03.500 --> 01:02:06.660
we feel them foremost in our mitochondria.

01:02:06.660 --> 01:02:08.780
And we need to integrate this information

01:02:08.780 --> 01:02:11.300
across maybe hundreds or thousands of mitochondria.

01:02:11.300 --> 01:02:13.940
And again, I'm thinking that fields are one way

01:02:13.940 --> 01:02:15.540
in which this can happen.

01:02:15.540 --> 01:02:18.300
And then this is a single cell like an amoeba cell.

01:02:18.300 --> 01:02:20.220
Then we have multicellular organisms,

01:02:20.220 --> 01:02:22.060
and now we've got cells to bring together

01:02:22.060 --> 01:02:23.580
all with these moving parts inside.

01:02:23.580 --> 01:02:25.780
And finally, a central nervous system,

01:02:25.780 --> 01:02:27.500
which amplifies all of this.

01:02:27.500 --> 01:02:30.380
So the communications, the electrical communications

01:02:30.380 --> 01:02:33.140
between single cells and their interface with the world,

01:02:33.140 --> 01:02:35.100
becoming incorporated into larger cells,

01:02:35.100 --> 01:02:37.780
incorporated into multicellular organisms,

01:02:37.780 --> 01:02:39.420
and finally into a central nervous system.

01:02:39.420 --> 01:02:41.820
This, I'm suggesting, is the substrate,

01:02:41.820 --> 01:02:45.180
which gives rise in the end to the complexity

01:02:45.180 --> 01:02:46.740
of our own consciousness.

01:02:48.780 --> 01:02:49.820
This is what I've said.

01:02:49.820 --> 01:02:51.060
Perhaps I don't need to say it again.

01:02:51.060 --> 01:02:52.380
I feel like I'm running out of time.

01:02:52.380 --> 01:02:55.060
So what I'm going to say instead is thank you

01:02:55.060 --> 01:02:57.580
to the guys in my lab who've been working on this.

01:02:57.580 --> 01:02:59.740
It's pretty brave for them to do it at all.

01:02:59.740 --> 01:03:01.660
This is, in fact, an old slide.

01:03:01.660 --> 01:03:03.940
They're holding the Krebs cycle, and I like that so much.

01:03:03.940 --> 01:03:06.860
It was a birthday present a few years ago that I've kept it.

01:03:06.860 --> 01:03:08.420
So half these guys have now left my lab,

01:03:08.420 --> 01:03:10.340
and I've had to put the ones who've joined

01:03:10.340 --> 01:03:12.100
since then around the outside.

01:03:12.100 --> 01:03:13.860
I suppose I'll have to change this at some point,

01:03:13.860 --> 01:03:19.020
but it's a brave thing to do a PhD on the origin of life.

01:03:19.020 --> 01:03:21.540
And I'm beginning to start thinking about doing experiments

01:03:21.540 --> 01:03:23.740
on consciousness, which is probably even more foolhardy

01:03:23.740 --> 01:03:25.220
